    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "A tip for MacOS on ARM (Apple Silicon): pypy is [not available in this platform](https://www.pypy.org/posts/2020/12/mac-meets-arm64-940822335619099039.html). The x64 version still works correctly thanks to macOS' Rosetta2, but it fails to load the rust-pyspec-glue module's native library, which gets built by default for ARM. \r\n\r\nI managed to fix this by cloning the [rust-pyspec-glue repo](https://github.com/petertdavies/rust-pyspec-glue), building it manually with `maturin build --target=x86_64-apple-darwin`, and `pip install` the resulting wheel.\r\n\r\nI am no Python expert so I fumbled around quite a bit to get this done; maybe I forget some intermediate step.\r\n\r\nIn any case, some rebust-ish instructions to run the tests on macOS would be great. I'm still on it...",
